Oh yeah Silbus, the Numenoreans <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  were</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> an interesting race indeed. The Numenoreans/1st age Adan were my favorite heros in ME. Hurin, Huor, Turin, Elros, Earndil the Mariner (Elrond and Elros's father), Tar-Aldarion 6th king of Numenor, etc etc. The most powerful humans of the time. The numenoreans were powerful in battle, and so badass that when they found out Sauron was on the move during the second age they simply landed an army, utterly destroyed his, marched on Mordor and took him away in chains. Of ocurse that was their eventual undoing. They should of slain him instead.<br>
<br>
The book unfinished tales has a chapter called the Disaster at the Gladden Fields. Its the story of how Isildur and his company were waylaid by orcs on the way to Arnor, and Isildur ultimately perished. But it gives a good description of how powerful the Numenoreans were in combat. It took many orcs to take down Isildur's small company of 100 numenoreans. The Numenoreans were also so doughty that the one ring had little effect on Isildur, although he was of high lineage, and had the wisdom/willpower not to wear the evil thing much.<br>
<br>
My kind of guys.<br>
<br>
read that story in Unfinished Tales. Its really good.<br>
